---
title: Butternut Squash Power Bowl with Farro, Pistachios, and Pickled Shallot
description: Treat yourself to a power half hour with this 30-minute meal that has some seriously nourishing ingredients. Between the vitamin A– and C–loaded butternut squash, fiber-packing farro, and mineral-rich pistachios, every bite is loaded with nutritious deliciousness. But this dish also goes beyond feel-good wholesomeness: thanks to pickled shallot and Parmesan, it’s got some swagger and bite, too.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/w10-r8-da59dacf.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/w10-r8-5a5ce8952c3e0834351eb4b1-2b3ba2b9.pdf
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/w10-r8-5a5ce8952c3e0834351eb4b1
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
time required: 40 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 570 kcal
  fat: 26 g
  saturated fat: 9 g
  carbohydrates: 72 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 19 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 360 mg
---

Adjust rack to middle position in #oven{} and preheat to 425 degrees. In a #medium pot{}, stir together @farro{3/4%cup}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and @water{3 1/2%cups}. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{30-35%minutes} total.

> TIP: If water evaporates before farro is done, add a splash more.

Wash and dry all produce. Toss @butternut squash{12%ounce} with a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} on a #baking sheet{}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Roast in oven until tender and browned, about ~{30%minutes}, tossing halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}(diced). Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}(thinly sliced). Finely chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}(finely chopped). Place shallot, @white wine vinegar{5%tsp}, and @sugar{1/2%tsp} in a #small bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to combine. Set aside.

Heat a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add @pistachios{1%ounce} and toss frequently until toasted and fragrant, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> TIP: If nuts seem like they might burn, remove pan from heat for a few seconds.

Remove from pan and set aside to cool. Roughly chop once cool enough to handle.

A few minutes before farro is done, heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in pan used for nuts over medium-high heat. Add onion. Cook, tossing frequently, until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add garlic and cook, tossing, until fragrant, ~{1%minute} more. Once farro is tender, drain any excess water, then toss into pan with onion and garlic. Stir in half the pistachios, half the @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}, and @butter{1%tbsp}. Remove pan from heat.

Add half the shallot and all of its pickling liquid to pan with farro. Toss to combine and melt butter. Season with salt and pepper. Divide farro mixture between #bowls{}{}. Top with squash. Sprinkle with remaining pistachios and Parmesan. Garnish with remaining shallot (if desired) and parsley.